# data-models

Primary Data Models:

1. Meeting Model
Importance Score: 95/100
- Title and metadata tracking
- Multiple note formats support (markdown, plain text)
- Signal tracking (decisions, actions, risks)
- Participant list with roles
- Integration with sprint/project context
- Link to knowledge graph nodes
- Custom fields for meeting intelligence

2. Document Model
Importance Score: 90/100 
- Versioned content storage
- Signal extraction results
- Tag-based categorization
- DIKW level classification
- Knowledge graph connections
- Source attribution tracking
- Custom metadata fields

Relationships:
- Meetings <-> Documents (many-to-many)
  - Meeting notes as documents
  - Referenced documents in meetings
  - Shared signal context

- Meetings <-> Signals (one-to-many)
  - Extracted decisions
  - Action items
  - Risks and blockers
  - Ideas and suggestions

- Documents <-> DIKW Items (one-to-many)
  - Knowledge hierarchy classification
  - Confidence scoring
  - Promotion tracking
  - Version history

